State of Connecticut v. Anita Wheeler (2999)

Hull, Boeden and Daly, Js.

Argued December 10 decision released December 31, 1985 Anita Wheeler, pro se, the appellant (defendant). John J. Nazzaro, special assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were Andrew Wittstein and Carl Schuman, assistant state’s attorneys, and Joseph Burns, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

There is no error.
